The paper deals with image compression using recurrent, convolutional neural networks, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of lossy compression, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM). The improvements made to the network architecture and training process involve modifications to the network's hidden state, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of entropy coding and bit allocation, which are topics in information retrieval (cs.IR) and information theory (cs.IT), respectively.
